# Batch Process ERC-7730 Registry Folder

When the user wants to process, migrate, or update an entire registry folder, use this tool. It orchestrates schema migration, test generation, and PR creation in one run.

## Command

```bash
node tools/scripts/batch-process.js <folder-name> [options]
```

## Batch Processor Options

| Option | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `--dry-run` | Preview changes without modifying files |
| `--verbose` | Show detailed output for each operation |
| `--skip-tests` | Skip test file generation |
| `--skip-migration` | Skip v1 to v2 schema migration |
| `--pr` | Create a branch and PR with changes (targets master) |
| `--pr-draft` | Create the PR in draft mode |
| `--pr-strict` | Prevent PR creation if any step fails |
| `--pr-title <title>` | Custom PR title |
| `--pr-branch <name>` | Custom branch name |
| `--local-api` | Auto-start local Flask API server for tester calls |
| `--local-api-port <port>` | Port for local API server (default: `5000`) |

## Cascaded Test Generation Options

These options are passed through to `generate-tests.js`:

| Option | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `--depth <n>` | Max transactions to search (default: `100`) |
| `--max-tests <n>` | Max tests to generate per function (default: `3`) |
| `--chain <id>` | Only process a specific chain ID |
| `--openai-url <url>` | Custom OpenAI API URL (e.g., Azure endpoint) |
| `--openai-key <key>` | OpenAI API key (overrides `OPENAI_API_KEY`) |
| `--openai-model <model>` | Model to use (default: `gpt-5`) |
| `--azure` | Use Azure OpenAI request format |
| `--no-test` | Skip running the clear signing tester |
| `--force-test` | Run tester even when test file already exists |
| `--device <device>` | Tester device: `flex`, `stax`, `nanosp`, `nanox` |
| `--test-log-level <lvl>` | Tester log level: `none`, `error`, `warn`, `info`, `debug` |
| `--no-refine` | Skip refining `expectedTexts` from tester output |

## Examples

Preview what will happen:

```bash
node tools/scripts/batch-process.js 1inch --dry-run --verbose
```

Full processing with PR:

```bash
source .env && node tools/scripts/batch-process.js uniswap --pr
```

Migrate only (no tests):

```bash
node tools/scripts/batch-process.js aave --skip-tests
```

Generate tests only (no migration):

```bash
source .env && node tools/scripts/batch-process.js protocol --skip-migration
```

Force-run tester with local API (no PR):

```bash
source .env && node tools/scripts/batch-process.js circle --local-api --force-test
```

Custom PR settings:

```bash
source .env && node tools/scripts/batch-process.js kiln --pr-title "Update Kiln descriptors" --pr-branch "feat/kiln-v2"
```

## Workflow

The script processes each ERC-7730 file in the target folder:

1. **Schema Migration** - Migrates v1 files to v2 format (linting/validation handled by `migrate-v1-to-v2.js`)
2. **Test Generation** - Creates missing test files from blockchain data
3. **PR Creation** (with `--pr`) - Creates a clean branch from `<remote>/master`, commits only the files modified by batch-process, and opens a PR targeting `master`

## Prerequisites

- Node.js v16+
- Environment variables for test generation: `source .env`
- Optional: `erc7730` Python CLI for linting
- Optional: `gh` CLI for PR creation
